  "text": "Cortisol is a stress hormone that mediates limbic arousal. A study that measured salivary cortisol after EFT showed that EFT reduces cortisol levels by 24% (p < 0.05 compared with controls). This reduction correlated with a statistically significant (p < 0.05) 58% reduction in anxiety scores. Control subjects receiving an interview or no treatment showed a 14% reduction in cortisol, which is consistent with physiologic decreases in cortisol that occur throughout the day [CITATION_1] . However, a subsequent study of patients suffering from tension headaches showed that while EFT treatment was associated with fewer (p < 0.001) and less severe headaches (p < 0.001), it did not reduce morning or evening cortisol measurements between the 2 groups (p = 0.791 and 0.196) [CITATION_2] .",
